if i do +yy in neovim, will that automatically put it on the system clipboard, or do I need to add wl-clipboard?

Gemini said
The short answer is: You still need to install wl-clipboard.

Neovim is the "brain," but it doesn't actually know how to talk to the Wayland compositor's clipboard on its own. It looks for a "provider" (an external helper program) to do the heavy lifting.

How it works under the hood
When you type "+yy, Neovim goes through a checklist:

Is the clipboard option set?

Is there a clipboard tool installed on the system?

If on Wayland, it specifically looks for wl-copy and wl-paste.

If wl-clipboard is not installed, Neovim will likely give you an error or simply do nothing when you try to use the + register, because it has no "bridge" to the system clipboard.

How to verify it's working
Once you've installed wl-clipboard with sudo pacman -S wl-clipboard, you can check if Neovim recognizes it by running this command inside Neovim:

Vim Script
:checkhealth provider
Look for the Clipboard section.

Success: It will say something like OK: wl-copy found.

Failure: It will say No clipboard tool found.

Summary Table
Requirement	Why?
wl-clipboard	The actual system tool that talks to Hyprland.
"+yy	The Neovim command to target the system register.
